{"type":"text","timestamp":1781081978903,"sessionID":"ses_14f3f0769ffee11K26pi9Ov89W","part":{"id":"prt_eb0c21e660018u2JiTlJ06YDZJ","messageID":"msg_eb0c212f6001R2a0c5fXU6y3mr","sessionID":"ses_14f3f0769ffee11K26pi9Ov89W","type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me verify the schema and check that an empty/baseline solution would score 0.\n\n- Reward formula: sum over tiers of `pass_rate(tier) * weight(tier)`, with weights ~1/3 each for tier1/2/3.\n- Each test is an exact byte-diff against the GNU `ls` oracle output. Per-test binary pass/fail.\n- If baseline `rls` doesn't exist or fails: actual_file is empty → diff fails → 0 pass.\n- Single metric per test (exact output match) — strong shortcut resistance.\n- Multi-dimensional: 3 tiers (basic, long, sorting), weighted equally. Tier1 (basic) is easiest. Agent could max it and skip others → arithmetic-mean-like vulnerability for ~33% score on easy dim alone.\n- compute_reward.py emits subscores=[] on failure, with score 0.0 — schema valid.\n- Scoring runs from subscores.txt — fully modular, doesn't import agent code.","time":{"start":1781081972326,"end":1781081978892}}}
