{"type":"text","timestamp":1781082018370,"sessionID":"ses_14f3f0769ffee11K26pi9Ov89W","part":{"id":"prt_eb0c2bff400190mSNpf1EixFRX","messageID":"msg_eb0c2aa64001wO8QArkoKCW88X","sessionID":"ses_14f3f0769ffee11K26pi9Ov89W","type":"text","text":"Reward design audit complete. Verdict: **WARN**.\n\nKey findings:\n- **Formula**: weighted sum of per-tier pass rates (1/3 each) where every test is a binary byte-exact diff vs GNU `ls`.\n- **Strong**: correctness gating (exact diff has no floor), implementation-agnostic (measures output not algorithm), shortcut-resistant (trivial outputs can't match), modular scoring (compute_reward.py reads only subscores.txt, never imports /app), and a valid `reward.json` schema in both paths.\n- **Concern (dimension_balance)**: equally-weighted weighted-sum across three tiers of unequal difficulty. tier1_basic is markedly easier than tier2_long_format — an agent that only nails basic listing pockets ~33% without touching long format or sorting. Suggested fix in notes: power-mean (p≤0) or cross-tier minimum-pass gate.\n\nOutput: `results/pre-qa/reward_design.json`.","time":{"start":1781082013685,"end":1781082018367}}}
